    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to a style of 19th- and early 20th-century Scottish pottery originally named for Lady Grosvenor of Wemyss Castle and characterized by flowers, fruit, or animals painted in bright colors on a white ground often in a sketchy style.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere al estilo de cerámica escocesa del siglo XIX y principios del siglo XX originalmente denominada por Lady Grosvenor del Castillo de Wemyss y caracterizada por flores, fruta, o animales pintados en colores luminosos sobre una base blanca a menudo en un estilo esbozado.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Keramiekstijl gekenmerkt door krachtige en fel geschilderde natuurlijke vormen, vervaardigd tussen 1883 en 1930 te Kirkaldy in Schotland.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指十九世紀和二十世紀初期蘇格蘭的陶器風格，最初因威姆斯城堡的格洛斯維諾夫人而命名。其特色為以鮮艷色彩於白色背景上繪製花、水果或動物等圖案，通常採素描風格。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
